12/12/2003
VIDIN, Bulgaria -- The Association for Cross-Border Co-operation and Development of Northwestern Bulgaria said Thursday (11 December) that it has been selected to conduct an anti-corruption project at border checkpoints next year.
The project will be carried out in the regions of Vidin, Calafat and Zajcar.
It would tighten public control over the everyday routine of customs officers and border police at the three crossings.
(Trud - 12/12/03;
BTA, BNT - 11/12/03)
